        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 100 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Beaverton, or 8 miles northeast of Sulligent, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Winfield, Haleyville, Guin, Brilliant, Beaverton, Gu-
Win, Brinn, Lake Buttahatchee, Bear Creek, Twin, Tucker, Henson
Springs, Tessner, Pearces Mill, Rankin Fite Airport, Upper Bear Creek
Reservoir, Marion County Public Lake, Piney Grove, and Pikeville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
